Release schedule, time-based
````````````````````````````

    [I]n this strategy a specific date is set for the release well in advance and a schedule created so people can plan accordingly. Prior to the release, there is a cut-off date on which all features are evaluated regarding the stability and maturity. Subsequently, a decision is made as to whether they can be included in the release or whether they have to be taken out again and can be considered for the following release.

    -- :cite:`glossary-Mich07` p. 45

